bib.title: Thulium-169 Neutron Inelastic Scattering Cross Section Measurements Via The 169Tm(N,N'Gamma) Reaction

free_txt: Corrected for:
. multiple scattering (using code PENHA-B),
. neutron and gamma attenuation (using code NEVES),
. fluence variation over sample due to angular
dependence of neutrons from source reaction.
Ge detector operated in conjunction with
NaI(Tl) annulus for suppression of Compton scattering
events.
Overall uncertainty given.
235U fission chamber used to
determine neutron fluence.
Plastic scintillator neutron monitor used to normalize
neutron scattering to fluence measurements.
Ge detector efficiency determined using calibrated
gamma-ray sources.
Thulium disc, containing 3.38E+23 nuclei.
Data received by email from Pilneyo Seo, 6 March 2003.
Approved by Pilneyo Seo, 10 March 2003.
At 750 keV, cross sections obtained using Legendre
polynomial fit to angular distributions; otherwise,
data are taken from 125 degree data, assuming
angular distributions are isotropic.
Computed by summing integrated gamma production cross
sections of all transitions originating from a given
level and subtracting those for transitions that feed
it.
